bilingual.source: He set a trap to catch the rat.
bilingual.target: 他设了一个陷阱来抓老鼠。

bilingual.source: There is a rat hole near the garage.
bilingual.target: 车库附近有一个老鼠洞。

bilingual.source: The rat chewed through the electrical wires.
The cat caught a rat in the garden.
bilingual.target: 猫在花园里抓到了一只老鼠。

bilingual.source: I saw a rat running across the kitchen floor.
bilingual.target: 我看到一只老鼠跑过厨房地板。

bilingual.source: The city took measures to prevent a rat infestation in the sewers.
bilingual.target: 城市采取措施防止下水道里老鼠的侵扰。

bilingual.source: Distinguish a friendly rat from a hostile one.
bilingual.target: 把友善的老鼠和不友善的老鼠区分开来。

bilingual.source: This rat detection method doesn't rely on specialist equipment.
bilingual.target: 这种老鼠检测方法不依赖专业设备。

bilingual.source: A rat will help another rat that has previously helped them.
bilingual.target: 一只老鼠会帮助另一只曾经帮助过它们的老鼠。

bilingual.source: For one thing, they help control the rat and mouse population.
bilingual.target: 首先，它们有助于抑制老鼠的数量。

list.abstract: rat，英文单词，名词、动词，作名词时意为“鼠；卑鄙小人，叛徒，人名；(法、意、印、瑞典)拉特；(泰)叻”，作动词时意为“捕鼠；背叛，告密”。
彭乔宇，游戏ID：Rat，出生于河南周口，中国《英雄联盟》电竞职业选手，司职ADC，现效力于UPA俱乐部 。 2020年1月，加入eStar英雄联盟分部。2021年6月，UPA公布2021LDL夏季赛大名单，彭乔宇担任ADC。

yingyinNormal.en: But the rat! You must... It stole my documents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是那老鼠... 你必须... 那老鼠偷了我的餐厅。

yingyinNormal.en: Would that be a giant rat's ass?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有没有巨型老鼠屁屁？

yingyinNormal.en: Our rat's just come out of his den.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的老鼠出洞了。

yingyinNormal.en: Sunshine, daisies, butter mellow. Turn this stupid, fat rat yellow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 阳光，雏菊，黄油飘香，快快把这笨老鼠变黄。

yingyinNormal.en: A rat bit her ass? Okay, 195.
yingyinNormal.zh: 老鼠咬她的屁股了? 好吧，便宜五块。

yingyinNormal.en: String? Yes! Playing dumb. Taunting me with that rat. Rat? Yes. He's consorting with it. Deliberately trying to make me think it's important. The rat. Exactly!
yingyinNormal.zh: 像操控木偶?对，把我当白痴耍，用只老鼠来愚弄我。老鼠? 对，他和一只老鼠狼狈为奸，误导我以为那老鼠很重要。那只老鼠？没错。

yingyinNormal.en: He's the big rat, rat number one. He's just done something very suspicious indeed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他是头号大老鼠，他刚做了非常可疑的事。

yingyinNormal.en: Ratatouille doesn't sound delicious. It sounds like "rat" and "patootie." Rat patootie. Which does not sound delicious.
yingyinNormal.zh: 法式杂菜煲听起来像老鼠加上杂七杂八的名字，法式杂菜煲不好听。

yingyinNormal.en: Have you had a pet rat? No. Did you work in a lab with rats? No. Perhaps you lived in squalor at some point? Nopety. Nopety. No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你该养过宠物鼠吧？没有。那实验室里老鼠呢? 没有。或许你就住在老鼠窝中？没有没有没有？

yingyinNormal.en: But there's a rat problem. Apparently, they're attracted to dryer sheets.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是现在有老鼠了，它们显然对烘干机里的香料纸感兴趣。

yingyinNormal.en: A rat appears on the boy's first night, I order him to kill it. And now he wants me to see it everywhere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 老鼠出现在男孩来求职的晚上我要他杀了它，想让我觉得鼠魂不散。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you know what would happen to us if anyone knew we had a rat in our kitchen? They'd close us down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果被人发现我们的厨房里有老鼠，你知道会有什么后果吗？勒令停业。

yingyinNormal.en: Is the rat important? Of course not! He just wants me to think that it is. Oh, I see the theatricality of it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那只老鼠重要吗? 当然不，他想让我认为重要，我知道其中的把戏。

yingyinNormal.en: You stick electrodes in a rat's brain, give him an orgasm button, he'll push that thing until he starves to death.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在老鼠大脑里插入电极，再给它个高潮按键，它会一直按着那个键直到死。

yingyinNormal.en: They think you might be a cook. But you know what I think, Linguini? I think you are a sneaky, overreaching little...Rat!
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许你是厨师的料，但你知道我怎么想吗？你这奸诈狡猾的... 老鼠。

yingyinNormal.en: That's just great, Riley, you just drove off a cliff. What kind of rat hole at the bottom of a cliff, are you gonna find for $17?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这下好了，莱丽，你刚开下悬崖。在悬崖底部的老鼠洞上哪去找十七块钱？

yingyinNormal.en: And the truth is, I have no talent at all. But this rat, he's the one behind these recipes. He's the cook. The real cook.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这事实就是 我一点天份也没有，这只老鼠才是食谱的创造者，它是不折不扣的厨师。

yingyinNormal.en: The only difference between us and the rat is that you can't stick an electrode in our hypothalamus. That's where you come in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们跟老鼠的区别就在于我们不能在我们视丘下部置入电极，所以你就派上用场了。

yingyinNormal.en: You can't keep a rat in your apartment. They're extremely unsanitary. I mean, they transmit leptospirosis and hanta virus.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不能在公寓里养老鼠，那很不卫生的，我是说，他们可能会传染细螺旋体病或是汉他病毒。

yingyinNormal.en: We can be the greatest restaurant in Paris, and this rat, this brilliant Little Chef, can lead us there. What do you say? You with me?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们可以成为巴黎最伟大的餐厅。而这只聪明的小老鼠可以帮助我们达成。你们认为呢？可以吗？

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a gnawing animal with brown, black, white, or grayish fur that looks like but is larger than a mouse

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Rats</highlight> have been shown to engage in multiple forms of reciprocal help and cooperation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 老鼠已经被证明参与了多种形式的互助和合作。

examination_example.sentence: Across 18 trials each, the living <highlight>rats</highlight> were 52% more likely on average to set the social robot free than the asocial one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在每18个试验中，活着的老鼠平均释放社交机器人的可能性比释放非社交机器人高出52%。

examination_example.sentence: During the experiment, the social robot rat followed the living <highlight>rats</highlight> around, played with the same toys, and opened cage doors to let trapped <highlight>rats</highlight> escape.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在实验中，社交机器鼠跟随活老鼠，玩同样的玩具，打开笼门让被困的老鼠逃走。
